# Nexora Core Back-End Standards

Refer to the root GEMINI.md for full standards.

Critical Back-End Rules:
1. GraphQL first: Update schema.graphqls before Java code.
2. Use Lombok (@Data, @Builder) to keep classes clean.
3. Feature-based packaging (e.g., com.nexora.core.content).
4. All entities must use UUID or Slugs for public identifiers.
5. Strict nullability in GraphQL: use ! for mandatory fields.
6. Handle N+1 problems in GraphQL resolvers proactively.
7. Snake_case for database mapping.
